@folke as I mentioned above, Neotest broke for me last week I believe due to this... I was able to rollback from nightly to stable and confirm it works as expected. BUT that does not guarantee this was the cause of it so I want to rollback to the commit before this one from last week (to confirm for the team if this indeed was the commit that broke Neotest for me).

Do you know if there is an archive anywhere of nightly installs to download / install or do I have to go the route of cloning the repo, switching to the commit I want, and doing an old fashioned build from source on my machine? Because I am on Windows and it is a bit of a nightmare to build on Windows 🤣  (I can, but I don't want to if there is something easier / quicker to get hold of a nightly from a few days ago). Thanks!

I just want to be able to give a definitive confirmation that this commit was the cause of the Neotest plugin breaking for me so the team has more info to go off of whenever they take a look here :-)

This is a huge breaking change and I feel it is unintuitive.

for example, given lualine.nvim as an example, the default configuration for the status bar is like this:


```lua
sections = {
    lualine_a = {'mode'},
    lualine_b = {'branch', 'diff', 'diagnostics'},
    lualine_c = {'filename'},
    lualine_x = {'encoding', 'fileformat', 'filetype'},
    lualine_y = {'progress'},
    lualine_z = {'location'}
  },
```

In the stable version, the user only need to rewrite `lualine_x` to whatever he likes and the things are done. Now, suppose if the user only wants two components in `lualine_x` and doesn’t want to included `filetype` in `lualine_x`, there’s no way for the user to actually to do it (unless he wrote some really hackish way like set the third index to a function that returns an empty string. But this only makes configuration more hackish and less intuitive).
